    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="278"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_JCS1">J.C.S.</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the British Chiefs of Staff</hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d278fn1">Noted by the Combined Chiefs of Staff at their
                        175th Meeting, September 15, 1944. See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_357">p. 357</ref>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_CCS1">C.C.S.</gloss> 682</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quebec</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-15">15 September
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Operation “<gloss target="#t_Highball1"
                        >Highball</gloss>”</hi>
                </p>
                <p>The American Chiefs of Staff are asked to take note that Operation <gloss
                        target="#t_Highball1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Highball</hi>
                    </gloss> will be available in the Eastern Theatre at the end of November,
                    1944.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
